                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>New York</placeName>
                                        <date>Dec 6. 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Rev Dr Leeser</addressee> Ed of the Occident</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">Enclosed find<lb/> a reply from <persName>Rev C. D
                                                  Oliver</persName>, of <placeName>Mont-<lb/>gomery
                                                  Ala</placeName> to the letter of <persName>Rev E
                                                  Marcus-<lb/>sohn</persName> to the Editor of the
                                        Jewish Chronicle <date>Sept<lb/> 16, 1852</date> as per
                                                  <date>Oct.</date> Occident which you will oblige
                                        the<lb/> friends in <placeName>Montgomery</placeName> by
                                        publishing<lb/> And allow me to say in this
                                        con-<lb/>nection, that whatever may have<lb/> been
                                                  <persName>Mr Marcussohn's</persName> motives,
                                        he<lb/> carried his self deception if we admit that<lb/> he
                                        was self-deceived to a remarkable extent<lb/> if we do not
                                        admit this, then he carried<lb/> out his deception of others
                                        to the same extent.<lb/> For the alternative present itself,
                                        that either<lb/> he was self-deceived, (this he denies) or
                                        he was deceiving others. For after he made<lb/> his
                                        profession of belief in the doctrines<lb/> of Christianity,
                                        to Christian parties in
                                                  <placeName>Mont<lb/>gomery</placeName>, we were
                                        solicited to do something<lb/> to aid him in a pecuniary
                                        way. We<lb/> proposed to the friends that if they could<lb/>
                                        recommend him to let him to work as<lb/> a missionary to the
                                        Jews, under our care<lb/> They recommended him. We made a
                                        proposal</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p>to employ him, as He accepted it, and soon<lb/> after entered the
                                        field under the supervision<lb/> of our missionary at
                                                  <placeName>Charleston</placeName>. As
                                        evi-<lb/>dence of the latter fact our Treasurer has<lb/>
                                                  settes<add>?</add> receipt for money received by
                                        him for his<lb/> labors, as a missionary, to convert the
                                        Jews to<lb/> Christianity. Of course we were gratified<lb/>
                                        at the conversion to our faith of a man<lb/> of <persName>Mr
                                                  Marcussohn's</persName> standing. We believed<lb/>
                                        him sincere, and acted accordingly<lb/> It was certainly a
                                        thing of his own seeking<lb/> not ours. Allow us to say Mr
                                        Editor<lb/> that our principle of action in our work<lb/> of
                                        converting Israelites to our faith is<lb/> based upon the
                                        firm conviction that<lb/> Christianity as found in the new
                                        Testament<lb/> is the religion of
                                                  <persName>Abraham</persName>
                                        <persName>Isaac</persName> &amp;
                                        <persName>Jacob</persName><lb/> and that Judaism, as now
                                        held, is not, hence<lb/> our anxiety respecting the
                                        salvation of Israel<lb/>ites. But our principles will not
                                        permit<lb/> us to make mere proselytes. We want only<lb/>
                                        those who thoroughly believe in intellect<lb/> and heart in
                                        the Christian religion, to join us<lb/> To make such
                                        converts is our aim. We<lb/> supposed <persName>Mr
                                                  Marcussohn</persName> such an one<lb/> and called
                                        him ours Now <persName>Mr M.</persName> finds<lb/> he was
                                        mistaken. Of course we are not about<lb/> condemning him for
                                        returning to his former faith<lb/> but he ought to have told
                                        the truth as it is</p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>and I am sure all parties would have<lb/> respected him more
                                        highly. We have<lb/> no disposition to injure <persName>Mr
                                                  M.</persName> No. No<lb/> God <sic>furbid</sic>
                                        but no one can blame<lb/> us for setting public opinion
                                        right as<lb/> to the course pursued by certain
                                        respecta-<lb/>ble clergymen whose statement respecting<lb/>
                                        <persName>Mr M's</persName> conversion have been so
                                        flatly<lb/> denied by him</p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">I remain as ever</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">Truly Yours</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">R McGregor</persName>
                                        Secy</p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">ASMC Jews</p>
                    </body>
